# recall eval gold-set — one JSON object per line (lines starting with # are comments).
# Fields: id, query (natural recall phrasing), expect (answer-distinct keywords; a hit counts as
# correct if its indexed text contains ANY of them), negative (true ⇒ should NOT match anything),
# note. Keywords are deliberately NOT query terms, so a match means the hit holds the real answer,
# not just lexical overlap. Labels are real decisions established in THIS repo's past sessions
# (see the project memory). Environment-specific: only meaningful on a machine with this history.
{"id": "glm-529", "query": "what did we decide about the GLM failures in prism", "expect": ["overload", "z.ai", "529", "transient"], "note": "GLM failures = z.ai overload 529, server-side not config"}
